&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with transaction cost analysis&amp;nbsp;(TCA)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with project management&amp;nbsp;tools and methodologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Git/Jupyter&amp;nbsp;skills are a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work closely with trading desks and understand detailed market structures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The HR Systems Associate is a global role that will work with HR Systems team to provide functional support to our HR systems (workday). &lt;br&gt;The ideal candidate will support business-as-usual (BAU) operations by managing and resolving Workday tickets, conducting testing for new features, and assisting with system implementations and enhancements.&lt;/p&gt;
